* CygUtils-1.3.2 for Windows *
==============================

What is it?
-----------
CygUtils: creating automatic configuration scripts

Description
-----------
The CygUtils package includes: - ascii: simple utility for displaying the ASCII character set - banner: prints a message to the terminal in large characters (contributed by Joerg Schaible) - conv: a utility for converting line endings between DOS and UNIX format - cygstart: a cygwin replacement for the windows 'start' command - d2u, dos2unix: a copy of conv which defaults to converting DOS->UNIX - dump: simple utility for displaying a nicely formatted hexdump of a file - getclip: copy Windows clipboard to stdout - lpr: spool a file to a windows printer (contributed by Rick Rankin) - mkshortcut: create a windows shortcut (contributed by Joshua Daniel Franklin) - putclip: copy stdin to the Windows clipboard - readshortcut: read a windows shortcut (contributed by Joshua Daniel Franklin) - realpath: convert pathname argument to absolute path, with all reference to `.', `..', and symlinks resolved. - u2d, unix2dos: a copy of conv which defaults to converting UNIX->DOS
	 
